Zamfara State Government has shut down all government offices, Ministries and MDAs across the state. Findings by The Nation revealed that Governor Bello Muhammad has been mostly indoors since he came back to the state last Thursday from a foreign trip after staying for a while in Abuja. The Governor attended the inspection of proposed quarantined coronavirus centre at the Federal Medical Centre, Gusau on Friday after his arrival in the state. The First lady Hajiya A’isha Bello Muhammad also cancelled a press briefing at the Governor’s private residence at exactly 3pm, an hour to the scheduled time. Commissioner of Police Usman Nagoggo banned all gatherings of more than 20 people across the state and ordered for decongestion of all police stations, including immediate release of all suspects with minor offences.